venue.name: Paradise Dynasty 樂天皇朝 (Paradise Dynasty)

tips.text: Get their Signature Dynasty Dumplings which has 8 unique flavors. The la mian with porkbone soup is gd too. Sister restaurant to Taste Paradise fine dining.
This small food court is indeed has many good food from laksa, soon kueh, penang chendol. However the seat is too limited, the portion is quite smaller than normal food court, but reasonable price.
Terribly delicious, adequately fatty cutlets are matched by the miso sauce and service (offset a little by the disconcerting habit of turning on the lights before closing time, like a club).
The hotel and facilities are supposed to be 5-star but large number of incentive groups participate at the time of our visit. Breakfast at the hotel abit noisy...
Rice too little.. Pls order more rice!
Fantastic Soba noodle restaurant. Admire the quality in preparing the ingredients
Basically you can't go wrong with anything here, except wait times should you choose to do a walk-in. Be sure to reserve a week or more in advance to avoid disappointment. you can SMS 96536464.
Tasty treats! Well worth trying out
After queuing for more than an hour, u can't possibly buy just one tart ($3.5)! Go for 6 ($19.5) or max out your limit of 12. Can be served room temperature, chilled or warm. It's worth the calories!
Try their "ayam penyet" and "iga bakar"
Great Italian bread selling here! I love it!
Always a joy when we go to lukes.  An awesome place for an intimate celebration
Marriott Cafe @ Singapore Marriott Hotel 's High Tea Featuring Delectable Buffet Spread of International and Local Cuisine. Indulge in local delights like Oyster Omelette, Satay and many more!
Recommended! Sooooo delish! I love to order set 2 ( toast w/ kaya&butter, 2 half-boiled egg and coffee/tea) and laksa set with homemade barley :)

tips.text: Senior Sous Chef Nicholas Owen and his team will delight grill fans with a hearty selection of wood-fired steaks and seafood.

Best Japanese restaurant in Singapore for the freshest sashimi.
The new menu after 1-month-closure for renovation offers more new dishes! Love the French food with a Japanese twist. Every single dish is enjoyable, one of fav fine dining resto in SG!
Fantastic food. My favourite Japanese restaurant in Singapore. Try the tuna salad with avocado and seaweed.
Chilli crab pizza is not bad but I think I would stick to the classics.
Pretty good Teochew fare. Highlight is the braised Irish duck which is very succulent. Cold crab ($90/kg) and crispy egg noodles also decent. Not a fan of the deep fried pork ball and ornee though.
Lobster mentaiko & ebi tempura& chawanmushi & Asahi

Chicken+mini rice burger+salad set is perfect for one!
One of the best salad place in town.
